SERVER:
A server is a computer that provides resources and services to other computer on
A network

DOMAIN NAME:
A domain_name is used as alias to server ip address,  cuz it is easy to remember
by humans

DNS TYPE RECORD:
The address record is an A record(Address record) which maps domain name to
ip address

WEB SERVER:
Handles http requests of the user, it serves static content, forward requests
to application server for dynamic content

APP SERVER:
App server execute back end logic of the web app, process dynamic content and
generate response to client requests and intercats with the database server

DATABASE SERVER:
Store, manage and provide app server, it is respoinsble for stroring and retrieves
information requested by the web app
